What the role is
Web Developer
What you will be working on
1. Work closely with product managers, UX designers and backend engineers to define and develop web applications for 2D and 3D map platforms;

2. Build and maintain extensible production-grade front-end code to translate product specification into fully functional interfaces for both desktop and mobile web browsers;

3. Conduct new web GIS technology exploration and create proof-of-concept.
What we are looking for
- Background in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Geospatial Science/Technology or equivalent;

- Preferably more than 2 years of experience as a web front-end developer;

- Proficient in multiple font-end languages and libraries (e.g., JavaScript, JQuery, HTML5/CSS3, WebGL, Vanilla.JS);

- Experience with Web GIS and mobile-responsive development will be an added advantage;

- Familiar with development version control tools (e.g., GitLab, GitHub);

- Strong analytical and problem-solving skills;

- Good communication and interpersonal skills.

- Successful candidate will be offered a 11-months contract.

What the role is
Backend Systems Engineer
What you will be working on
- Participate in the implementation of a cloud based infrastructure for operating 2D and 3D map platform;
- Work within in an agile framework to ensure operational stability and performance through continuous optimisation;
- Assist in improving the operations of services, e.g., monitoring, alerting, metrics, logging and troubleshooting.
What we are looking for
- Background in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Geospatial Science/Technology or equivalent;
- Broad experience in a variety of backend technologies such as REST APIs, Shell Script, Node.JS, caching, databases, container/docker, deployment pipelines, systems monitoring, etc.;
- Hands-on experience working with AWS (S3, RDS, CloudWatch, EKS, etc.);
- Good working knowledge of Linus operating system (Ubuntu, RHEL, etc.)
- Can-do attitude, humility and open mindedness.
- Suitable candidate will be offered a 11-month contract.

What the role is
API Developer
What you will be working on
- Design and develop robust and scalable API services to support various location-based applications in operation;
- Test and improve APIs to ensure quality response time, reliability, correct record counts and data accuracy.
What we are looking for
- Background in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Geospatial Science/Technology and equivalent;
- Experience in designing and creating RESTful Web API and Microservices;
- Strong understanding of one or more of the following languages and frameworks: JavaScript, Java, Node.JS, relational (e.g., PostgreSQL) and non-relational databases (e.g., MongoDB);
- Strong knowledge of HTTP, REST, and JSON are crucial;
- Experience with API management or API gateway product and AWS service is a plus;
- Familiar with development version control tool (e.g., GitLab, GitHub);
- Good team player, with strong analytical skills and enjoys complex problem solving with innovative ideas.
- Suitable candidate will be offered a 11-months contract.

What the role is
Energy powers our economy, lights up our city and connects us all. Join the team keeping Singapore’s future alight and help us power tomorrow.

The Energy Market Authority is seeking dynamic and talented individuals to join us in the exciting energy sector - to ensure a reliable and secure energy supply, to promote effective competition in the energy market, and to develop a dynamic energy sector.
What you will be working on
As a digital communications intern, you will help assist in public communications efforts of EMA’s work to both external and internal stakeholders.

This includes:
• Production of digital newsletters and public education collaterals;
• Content ideation and development of social media assets for EMA’s online platforms;
• Development of research and media reports;
• Organising events and visits;
• Assisting in website management; and
• Perform administrative and any other duties assigned by the department.
What we are looking for
We are looking for a tech-savvy team player with:

• A flair for web-based communications and a keen eye for design;
• Proficiency in Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator and InDesign) a plus, but not compulsory;
• Good organisational skills and attention to detail;
• Excellent written and spoken communication skills; and
• Good interpersonal skills.

What the role is
At IRAS, we aim to be a leading tax agency known for our efficient services, expertise and integrity.

We are looking for committed team players to be involve in the SDLC process and to implement application changes in the new ICT System.

By being part of our internship programme, you will have the opportunity to:

- Learn how IRAS applies technology by participating in an agile development team for one of the initiatives below;

- Build on a wide spectrum of core technology skills, which may include microservices, DevSecOps and cloud usage;

- Experience IRAS’ work environment and culture first-hand.
What you will be working on
- Implement application enhancements to support co-existence with the new tax system;

- Support the data migration activities for major system transformation/modernisation programme;

- Perform programme/component design, coding, configuration, testing and other related tasks during project development;

- Analyse and resolve technical issues arising from development and testing;

- Support functional, non-functional and integration testing;

- Ensure system quality, security and application code performance; and

- Provide documentation on code components and libraries.
What we are looking for
- Commitment Period: At least 6 months

- A passion for technology and a willingness to learn;

- Team players who are self-motivated, adaptable, resilient with good interpersonal communication skills;

- Coding background and knowledge of Microsoft.NET/.NET Core Framework, ASP.NET, C#, XML, Web services, MS SQL, other ER databases.

- 6 vacancies available

